CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 3, 1946, pg.8, reads: "Summer Bride - Mrs. Dorothy Jackson Walker, YMCA secretary, one of the prettiest brides of the season, is pictured in her nuptial attire. The charming lady became the bride of Wayne Walker, son of Mrs. Ada Richmond of Race Street, last Thursday afternoon at eh home of Mrs. Samuel Wynn of Iowa Street.  Mrs. Walker is the daughter of Mrs. Olive Jackson of 2600 Wylie Avenue. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of bride Dorothy Jackson wearing gown with sweetheart neckline, seated in domestic interior
